{
  "texts": [
    "Comparatively, Samuelson's contribution to the development of EMH is less well-known, but his role is no less important as he provided a solid theoretical basis for this hypothesis.",
    "Since then, many studies have been published on examining whether the EMH is valid in different markets, for example, stock market (Lee et al., 2010; Sánchez-Granero et al., 2020), energy market (Lee and Lee, 2009; Liu et al., 2020), currency market (Potì et al., 2020).",
    "The idea behind testing EMH is to measure whether a random market walk is related to price predictability.",
    "For this purpose, different kinds of tests for market efficiency have been proposed addressing the concept of random walk (Frunza, 2016).",
    "However, there exists enough evidence to infer that the existence of an efficient market seems to be a utopia in practice."
  ]
}